The paper deals with the problem of making relational GroupBy over floating-point formats bit-reproducible, which is a topic related to database systems (cs.DB) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The authors also mention their effort to extend database engines with data representations more suitable for machine learning and scientific applications, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves modifying existing algorithms to make them more efficient, which could be related to data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG).
